faq.description: Do you have a question about our streaming service, or are you experiencing technical difficulties? See our most frequently asked questions below.

questions.answer:
The most current versions of the following browsers are recommended: 

  • Google Chrome

  • Mozilla Firefox

  • Apple Safari

  • Microsoft Edge

  • iOS and Android mobile browsers

For Android devices, we recommend minimum device specs of 3GB RAM, and 1.4GHz processor speed.For iPhone devices we recommend iPhone 12 or later. For desktops, we recommend systems with a dedicated graphics card.
questions.question: What are the system requirements?

questions.answer: You will require a Wi-Fi or broadband internet connection (DSL/cable or higher) with a minimum download speed of at least 1.2Mbps with latency not exceeding 100ms for SD and 4Mbps with latency not exceeding 50ms for HD (mobile data may not be supported). When traveling abroad, please connect to a Wi-Fi network or broadband connection to purchase and view the pass, avoid additional charges and ensure compatibility (this enables recognition of your current country as an eligible territory). Passes purchased in your home country remain accessible while you're abroad.
questions.question: What are the internet connection requirements?

questions.answer: During the game, please report your technical issues as a support ticket or email us at support@eluv.io. If there are no issues with the broadcast, we will need to complete troubleshooting steps. These may involve confirming details about the device, software, and your internet connection. *Please note that you must ensure you use compatible technology before purchasing a live subscription.
questions.question: I am having issues with my video or audio feed. What can I do?

questions.answer:
Refunds can only be issued for those who have reported a technical issue during the game which proves to be a fault of our providers and cannot be rectified. Please note that if you do not watch a stream through Choice or don’t report a technical issue to customer service during the game, we will not be able to issue a refund.

Refunds will not be issued for supporters attempting to access via a VPN.
questions.question: How do I get a refund?

questions.answer: EPCR monitors all game feeds. It has a strict monitoring policy and will prosecute individuals who illegally stream live games. We ask anyone who observes these feeds to inform us by emailing support@eluv.io or creating a support ticket anonymously.
questions.question: Can I share my match stream?

questions.answer: Is your connection fast enough? Try to stop all current downloads, torrents, or video streams and visit http://www.speedtest.net. Test your download speed. Results should show a minimum of 2Mbps to process streamed content along with usual browsing activities.
questions.question: My feed keeps buffering. What’s wrong?

questions.answer: The live video player will only be live during a match. If the game has kicked off and you are receiving this message, please create a support ticket or email support@eluv.io.
questions.question: I am receiving a “Media not available” message.

questions.answer: If the pass was purchased before or during the match, the match will be available for replay until 10 hours after the end of the match.
questions.question: Can I re-watch a match after it had ended?

questions.answer: To cancel your subscription, please create a support ticket or email support@eluv.io with your cancellation request. Please be advised that five working days' notice is required for cancellation. Cancellation within this period may result in your being charged for the next period.
questions.question: How do I cancel my subscription?

questions.answer:
If you've forgotten your password then please click on the relevant links on the login screen.

If you have any further queries, please create a support ticket or email support@eluv.io.
questions.question: I have forgotten my password.

questions.answer: Coverage is sourced from the world feed, offering English commentary for select games. EPCR Challenge Cup games produced in non-English-speaking territories may be provided without commentary.
questions.question: Why are the commentaries of the game I'm watching available in English only or without commentary?
